\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
Throughout, we consider a setting with a single instrument, treatment, and
 outcome:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
Y_{i} & =\alpha+\beta_{i}D_{i}+\eta_{i}\\
D_{i} & =\alpha+\gamma Z_{i}+\upsilon_{i}
\end{align*}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset Formula $D_{i}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $Z_{i}$
\end_inset

 are dummies for treatment and instrument
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset Formula $\beta_{\bm{i}}$
\end_inset

 a random coefficient that can differ across 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Important: outcome can in principle depend on both treatment and instrument:
 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
Y_{i}(d,z)
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
We want to estimate ATE:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\mathbb{E}\left[\beta_{i}\right]
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame
\begin_inset Argument 4
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
First Stage, Independence and Exclusion
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
For reference, consider first the case 
\begin_inset Formula $\beta_{i}=\beta\ \forall i$
\end_inset

.
 Assume:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Independence:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\left[\left\{ Y_{i}(d,z)\ \forall\ d,z\right\} ,D_{1i},D_{0i}\right]\perp Z_{i}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset Formula $Z_{i}$
\end_inset

 as good as random, 
\begin_inset Formula $D_{1i},D_{0i}$
\end_inset

 are potential outcomes for first stage
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Vietnam lottery example: 
\family roman
\series medium
\shape up
